  "summary": "Dr. Castells and Sattler discuss the hypnotic influence of Mrs. Carmichael, noting her Eastern ancestry and her motive to render Arthur Carmichael an incurable idiot to secure property for her son. Dr. Castells plans to have Mrs. Carmichael leave Walden on September 18th to escape a \"terrifying specter.\"\n\nOn September 14th, a maid reports that Arthur fell into a pond after his flat-bottomed boat tipped over. Dr. Castells, Sattler, and Felicity rush to the scene and find Arthur's seemingly lifeless body on the shore. After Dr. Castells performs CPR for an hour, Arthur regains consciousness, though he is confused and believes the date is August 12th. He recalls a terrifying dream in which he transformed into a cat, though the details remain elusive.\n\nAs they lead Arthur toward the house, Lady Cammichael appears in the hall. Upon seeing Arthur, she reacts with extreme terror and guilt, screams, and collapses. Dr. Castells determines she has died from shock, suggesting a \"one life for another\" exchange. Dr. Castells later informs Sattler that Arthur was actually murdered with cyanide.\n\nWhile the public explanation will be that Arthur suffered amnesia and his wife died of a fit of madness, Dr. Castells and Sattler hold secret knowledge. They note a torn chair in the hallway and discover that the missing book from the study was an ancient treatise on transforming humans into animals. Dr. Castells concludes that Felicity will keep the true secrets of the past weeks buried to protect Arthur.",
